3. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper may involve some computational aspects related to elliptic curve cryptography. 
4. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper may discuss the societal implications of the security flaws in the signcryption scheme. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper may involve the implementation of the signcryption scheme and the vulnerabilities in the software.
